column1: Where Bitcoin, supply chains, and COVID-19 intersect,"
Weekly research and insights on blockchain
Supply Chains in Chaos: The Coronavirus Impact on Bitcoin Mining
Last month, the Bitcoin network's hashrate fell 40% — the largest drop in 9 years.

We're living through a time in which several relatively unprecedented factors may be impacting Bitcoin miners. The third halving event in Bitcoin history is coming next month; a global pandemic is disrupting supply chains; markets appear to be experiencing a kind of financial contagion never before seen in Bitcoin's history.
The SFOX research team has compiled everything you need to know about the ways in which COVID-19 and the halving may interact to impact the Bitcoin mining industry.

Okay, fine. Technically it’s been spring for a minute now, but Supreme is making it official with the release of seven new tees as a part of their SS20 Week 8 drop. This season’s tee release features a strong showing of new logos including a chrome logo and a painted Supreme logo on the Sailboat Tee.

Both StockX and Supreme’s in-store operations are still closed so know that we won’t get same day product photos like we usually do. But don’t let that slow you down, shop all seven tees and the rest of Supreme SS20 Week 8 below!

Cactus Plant Flea Market’s popular and somewhat controversial Born Again Hoodie had a big day last week, restocking in every colorway previously released and dropping several new colorways. This release and restock brought the total number of existing colorways of the elusive hoodie to 10, all of which could be bought at once as a part of the brand’s $2,400 collector’s edition. Last year the hoodie was mistakenly thought to be a dig on Kanye West (which the brand has denied) but Drake has still been seen wearing it to death. Shop all ten colorways of the hoodie below!

But when you toss that takeout box on the coffee table and dig in without taking your eyes off the TV, you're doing yourself a disservice. Growing up, setting the table might have been a chore—but now, it's a little way to change up your atmosphere. As Caleb Pershan wrote in Eater, ""Regaining that feeling of ceremony associated with a restaurant meal might be as simple as getting out the good plates and the nice olive oil.""

So next time you order in, swap your to-go containers for real dishes, light a candle or two, put on some music <http://click.app.postmates.com/ls/click?upn=rnaAoWxiqCeuewRYPwxjBlYanerYfSiPEICp0Js10oJR9vQcuPt6pl1IkKnudWUwhJSSM9r1f3E6mtuy4wmrODobCTHrUk-2FWQBuUhFKzPOeG-2FEk2pD1jvA6mYZZpYDQhFjG4_s8pHtPQ1yS8IyZYRnkhHXi1R7rjwP3EeK1DGHF-2FXa-2Bj-2B2fnOJ8Z2x1t95eVeBtab0QU-2Fyj8zmUEl19fEgUFmR9bua3IV1SHUC0JLRd-2BnAUlrEea6MCrIv1jWeWuZMSqc1IrdjHNr9nxnc1Ej9IaJEamkOEF8kKs99xy-2BieSC2FUUyoU86OMXbbUFlGtZV3-2FLvc6NgRoEp-2FA7eEYxAtZGO3ijtQnt8UWCv2-2FnepqkJj6-2BTNETHmWNptv4xfXoqVDEwhp1oSEhmpwC9B77Tao9PHQ8-2Fe64BrVGchgbL9DxjDQd2VgZeHJKF0-2FoVilazTLo7oisXBDVXcOfP71tpT3DO9XzaDMzx8cFa2djVPStVoqg6PFCp8H0AlcatUFjC0wRl2smXo616yr9fREW3cWlFzxha2ekeaqwXI9sxT5HR8D-2FOzEvdTfIvTkCZ4KncG5FUP-2BZ04mjQ5r1gBwaL5m10fERbLORk0NhFaHpfY0HYvLd7o1Ww7SY-2BFGDajC542tdgQFCNXFISD-2F9zCRFGSZ5IDO6p1UhyEVrrKt4BAqWsHDGxETd5e28vJ2DMlYF7KKVie7AbYgASTyk6f4FC0c4Vayf0qu13ytrrMg62kzc9REfghddWxX0-2BM-2BjY5uu38HAL-2F7aM3S5Oc1X6lvKcefLs7mWIJRrTaH0f6MUShcO2nahLCTgPgmq8Itfa7LfjbaqhYoA0aWUjGDe2GgqC9csJA7KUsAIsg0yIS3i9SS2odlZo0NZpU93-2FqN3PlFgI44KQfyTF6HJOcoHqnU346N2KQ-3D-3D> , and line up your silverware on a napkin. Suddenly your kitchen table is a world away from your living room.
Archival Footage Is a Genre Now

It's impossible to know when your next live, packed, sweaty concert experience will be. And when you mix that uncertainty with the music industry's decades of recorded tracks and concerts, what do you get? The rise of the archive.

With legions of fans and a never-ending catalog of live music, the Grateful Dead were the obvious band to kick off this new trend. Shakedown Street is a new weekly livestream that will share a full gig every Friday for Dead Heads everywhere to tune into together. The National is also getting in the mix with archival footage streaming every Monday night—and the proceeds will go to their tour crew.

You now have unlimited collaborators in private repositories,
column2: We introduced a few changes to make all of the core GitHub features free for everyone.

column1: We introduced a few changes to make all of the core GitHub features free for everyone. Private repositories with unlimited collaborators are now available for all GitHub accounts, and we’re reducing prices for some of our paid plans.

column2: We introduced a new GitHub Free plan for teams with unlimited collaborators in private repositories, 2,000 GitHub Actions minutes/month, and GitHub Community Support.
You now have unlimited collaborators in private repositories as part of your GitHub Free plan.
Monthly pricing for our Pro plan has been reduced from $7/month to $4/month.
Monthly pricing for our paid Team plan has been reduced from $9/user to $4/user.
Actions minutes and Packages storage will continue to be free for all public repositories.

column1: Take a look at our FAQ or compare plans <https://github.com/pricing?utm_source=announcement&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=mnch-free>  on our pricing page for more information on these changes.

column1: Remember when you used to say goodbye to your SO at the door as one or both of you went to work? Now when that happens, it’s just in your kitchen—after breakfast and before you retire to your opposite sides of the WFH couch.

Being quarantined with your partner comes with all sorts of challenges and opportunities. We recommend embracing this time with some quality streaming and ordering in, but even that can lose its luster after a while.

That’s when you should consult this list of 17 activities to keep things interesting (because you always wanted to learn how to whittle anyway). And if you just need a gut check on how everyone else is doing, this wedding photographer <http://click.app.postmates.com/ls/click?upn=rnaAoWxiqCeuewRYPwxjBqJ5l8eD28KvznFBzLCBtnC5-2F-2BP7a4m5j9lRwCJERAm0Bu-2FnHoGuXZAs8-2F7KGuSUZvqTP0nbScwccBmxS5F8nJY-3DNVx1_s8pHtPQ1yS8IyZYRnkhHXi1R7rjwP3EeK1DGHF-2FXa-2Bj-2B2fnOJ8Z2x1t95eVeBtab0QU-2Fyj8zmUEl19fEgUFmR9bua3IV1SHUC0JLRd-2BnAUlrEea6MCrIv1jWeWuZMSqc1IrdjHNr9nxnc1Ej9IaJEamkOEF8kKs99xy-2BieSC2FUUyoU86OMXbbUFlGtZV3-2FLvc6NgRoEp-2FA7eEYxAtZGO3ijtQnt8UWCv2-2FnepqkJj7XAvu08h5-2BcuxKw0U6Iy2w8rO4bqgZUYK7YrOmALS4c1TkWIrdPsCt5559GlSOTAM7ecNJAdC2Dnnj3OXTvlYpQncgPZRlRHQMhgGF2GgtulrSC2rp9KYhTFjl6LXHExxrjRwa2qDfiz-2B1Pk6v2mCRLtclDcIbbG9SHroiAcP5Lzn2oOhl83Bpq-2FWjgxLbUHFlkjxhXPhBjYsBz-2FcnZ-2BqwATf2EKInV-2F0Ill5mhVK7MvCz0Plwob9RoCm-2BygzhFx8JWHTGnpnl9XsYTtxq0J2TyeUBP3QeXlQ2V973qSil8OazR0z8-2FG1vxRu8jLA9BS7UrBcfWT-2Bdc4kXIyESpPcXQCAwL9m1sxRaZZdqC4KVD-2BGGmp3Az1gQL5mYCxrERrjkSFrOp1DBQXcmAOz8CHp4p4GlnsRxMy4GRe1xFyOiiwMmlMAZcm9TwfQw1hFEk7m-2BH3WPj-2BeE4rG-2FFGEUqxEAvXSC2PieEzZZh19DpurfguW0vu-2BTqKCSIqa2i-2F-2FaA09c6DC65dBw1smBxrfFu5oKaPMmEy6NdsAo6Mzx7woSNg-3D-3D>  did the hard work for you by checking in with her former clients/current quarantined couples.

column1: Officials have confirmed that corona is spreading at an “exponential rate.”
Funny thing about stuff that is exponential.
Ever hear of the fact that if you could keep folding a paper over itself 56
times it’ll be thick enough to reach the sun?
The same is true of this coronavirus.
If 2 infect 4 which infect 8 which infect 16 you’ll quickly be at millions... and it’ll only take about 12 steps to get there...
Who’s going to come in to “handle” a million-person wide outbreak?
Because a National Guardsmen just broke rank with his organization and
shared the truth about coronavirus and what you can do about it. <http://immediatelyimportant.com/I6Nl9d.phtml?c8xFjbccdktTcw1Nfccc8jcJcvSSFcq9vcbbb2R>

The least you can do is hear him out.

column1: Drive thrus aren’t what they used to be. Traditionally used as a way to pick up some fast food (and the occasional Las Vegas wedding), sitting in your car has become the new way to party. Creative groups of friends and families all over the country are using drive thrus to celebrate every possible occasion.

Take a look at this socially distanced baby shower in Pennsylvania. How can you not be cheerful with that many pink balloons? Congrats goes out to the happy couple, and to those fast-thinking relatives who were still able to make it a memorable day.

Biscuits are the ultimate feel-good food. It’s like eating a flakey pillow that instantly makes your day better, and you should do it more often. Just thinking about these titans of carbs is probably putting you in the mood for 2 or 3 (maybe some gravy too, why not?).
Here's a look at a few of our favorite fluffy foods you can get all over the country.

The Flying Biscuit Cafe in Atlanta has a lot more than just biscuits on the menu, but you’re going to want to go full comfort with the Country Eggs Benedict. It’s a split biscuit topped with chicken sausage, over medium eggs, and chicken sausage gravy—plus a side of creamy dreamy grits.

In Austin, TX, Bird Bird Biscuit is serving up the ultimate breakfast menu. We recommend you try the Queen Beak Biscuit. It’s a hot combo of spiced and breaded chicken thigh, cayenne black pepper honey, and bacon-infused chipotle mayo, all piled high on the perfect homemade biscuit.

Chicken meets biscuit in the most delicious way possible at Bobwhite Counter in New York’s Alphabet City. At this back-to-basics neighborhood joint, chicken biscuits can be personalized with plenty of sauces and toppings, just make sure you add some Pimento Cheese if you know what’s good for you.

column1: Need someone new to talk to? How about someone who’s a great listener, always thirsty, and green? It’s a plant. You want a plant.

The less time you’re able to spend outside, the more important it is to bring some of that nature into your home. Enter plants. They don’t just look pretty—they also help you concentrate and increase your happiness. The appeal has grown so much recently that people are buying them in bulk online.

Another trend that’s growing? Growing (your own food, that is). If you’ve ever wanted to tend to a garden in your backyard, now is definitely the time. Follow these instructions and start with something simple like basil. It’s the kind of hobby you can eat, so we’re all for it.

But you can’t talk about plants without taking a moment to remember those we left behind. Office plants, you served us well. You were right there next to our monitors for years, smiling at us and ingesting just enough water to keep us distracted. We’ll miss you, tiny succulent and over-trimmed bonsai, but we’ll never forget you.

When lunchtime rolls around, there’s only one clear option. It’s the almighty sandwich. Two pieces of bread and a little imagination—that’s all it takes to make a memorable midday meal. There are a few tasty sandwiches we wish were in front of us right now. Check them out:

column1: In the mood for chips and cookies? That’s not what you’re going to find at this vending machine in Kansas City. It’s sitting in front of Jones Bar-B-Q and that means it’s full of—you guessed it—burnt ends and housemade sausage.

This is just one example of restaurants getting super creative with the new COVID-19 policies. Take O’Shea’s in West Palm Beach, FL. As we settle into the new realities of social distancing, our top priority is to be here for you - our customers, fleet, and local businesses.
From increased safety measures to supporting local businesses, we thought it would be a good time to share a few updates with you.

column2: Always follow guidance from the CDC on face masks, even when collecting your items; follow their tips on keeping your home hygienic and know what to do if you or a loved one gets sick.
While we continue to serve our customers, we’ve also been supporting people who need it most, including delivering meals to nurses caring for COVID-19 patients through Feed Hero Nurses.

We’ve provided support to the United Nations COVID-19 Solidarity Fund to get much-needed equipment to health workers and we’re working with the International Rescue Committee to gift Postmates credits to refugees. You can read more about these organizations and how you can help here.

This week we announced a package of new benefits that support our fleet including the industry's first family care policy for our workers. We're expanding the Postmates Fleet Relief Fund to now include a stipend for couriers to cover up to two weeks of childcare costs and related family emergency expenses.

Second, we announced new partnerships with telehealth platforms in order to connect couriers with important health care services free of cost. We are also issuing new reusable and single-use masks for couriers across the country.

Third, Postmates is helping merchants and fleet workers unlock federal funds available to them through the CARES Act. This builds on programs we launched last month including non-contact delivery and a benefits relief fund.
Our mission has always been local first and we are happy to have seen the number of new merchants joining Postmates increase by nearly 10X over the past month.

We recently launched our #OrderLocal campaign, a merchant relief pilot, and have partnered with Womply to help our small businesses navigate federal stimulus relief. So far over a thousand merchants have used this resource to apply for more than $50M in federal support.

column1: We will continue to keep you updated on everything we’re doing to keep the platform running as safely and smoothly as possible.
Thank you for being a continued part of the Postmates community.

? Now Available: Bodega S/S 2020 Drop 1 ?,The latest from the Bodega team

Bodega’s vision has always been 20/20, but even we were a little taken aback by the added relevance and strange timeliness of our SS20 collection. Call it prophecy, call it happenstance, call it coincidence. Regardless, the timing is right for right now. Mixing a grounded edge of spirituality and good fortune, Bodega’s newest tees promote positivity, hope, well-wishing, and worldwide community with street-level sensibilities, provocative, cutting-edge graphics and signature slogans.

It seems like we’ve got nothing but time on our hands. So why not spend it like we did in those carefree days of our youth— by completing the artistic creations of others. In Between the Lines: A Bodega Coloring Book features some of our favorite street artists presenting their edgy, updated takes on a truly classic childhood activity.
In tender times like these, its good to know who’s got your back. Thank you for having ours.
